Though this was probably a requisite, even short term lockdowns, quarantine and social distancing can precede long term effects such as symptoms of mental stress and disorder, including insomnia, anxiety, depression, and post-traumatic stress symptoms (
 Wang et al., 2020; 
 Brooks et al., 2020). Although there is a deluge of studies published regarding COVID-19, there is a paucity of published data regarding the mental health status of the general population.
